# Main.elm — EARLY

TEA bootstrap for the standalone LynRummy Elm game. Wires
the model + Msg + update + view into `Browser.element`.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Active churn — most file edits during
  port work land here. Stable shape but expanding scope.
- **Source:** new Elm file (no 1:1 TS source). Conceptually
  replaces `plugin.ts`'s host-bootstrap role.

## Current scope

Model:

```
Model = { board : List CardStack
        , hand  : Hand
        , drag  : DragState
        }
```

DragState carries `source` (`FromBoardStack Int` |
`FromHandCard Int`), `cursor`, `originalCursor`,
`grabOffset`, `wings`, `hoveredWing`, `overBoard`,
`boardRect`, and `clickIntent : Maybe Int` (cardIndex within
the source stack, only ever `Just _` when source is a board
stack).

Msg:

- `MouseDownOnBoardCard {stackIndex, cardIndex} Point` —
  fired by per-card mousedown. Both drag and click intents
  begin here; `clickIntent = Just cardIndex` is recorded
  optimistically and may die during MouseMove.
- `MouseDownOnHandCard Int Point` — hand-card drag start;
  no click semantic, `clickIntent = Nothing`.
- `MouseMove Point` — updates cursor; calls
  `GestureArbitration.clickIntentAfterMove` to maybe-kill
  the click intent.
- `MouseUp` — click takes precedence: if `clickIntent` is
  still `Just _` AND source is `FromBoardStack`, commits a
  split via `GestureArbitration.applySplit`. Otherwise falls
  through to wing-merge / place-as-singleton / snap-back
  branches.
- `WingEntered WingId` / `WingLeft WingId` — hover state on
  drop targets.
- `BoardEntered` / `BoardLeft` — track whether cursor is over
  the board (for hand-card place-as-singleton on MouseUp).
- `BoardRectReceived (Result … Element)` — `Browser.Dom.getElement`
  resolves on hand-drag start; rect cached for later
  cursor → board-relative coord translation.

## Subscriptions

`Browser.Events.onMouseMove` and `onMouseUp` are subscribed
ONLY while `drag = Dragging _`. Idle-state subscription is
empty.

## View composition

- Two-column flex shell: hand column (min-width 220px) left,
  board column (min-width 560px) right. Per memory
  `feedback_hand_upper_left`.
- `View.boardShellWith` carries `id="lynrummy-board"` for
  `getElement`, plus mouseenter/leave handlers.
- Each board card carries its own mousedown handler via
  `View.viewStackWithCardAttrs`. The stack div itself has
  no listener — the inversion described in
  `showell/claude_writings/splitting_a_stack.md`.

## Concession

Click UI is sub-optimal (TS literal `1`-pixel threshold;
fragile under jitter). Steve knows; preserved faithfully per
the bar-for-done. See `LynRummy/GestureArbitration.claude`.

## Pointers

- Hosted at `index.html` in this dir; built into `elm.js`
  via `npx elm make src/Main.elm --output=elm.js` (run
  automatically by `ops/start`).
- Served through Gopher at
  `http://localhost:9000/gopher/lynrummy-elm/`.
- Standalone-served at `http://localhost:8788/` if a Python
  http.server is running here.
